  "timeframe": "1H / 5m",
  "market_context": "On GC1! (Gold futures) around Tue 26 Nov, a daily candle 2 closure set up an hourly bullish setup. Price retraced into an hourly t-spot zone with a fair value gap, and the analyst dropped to the 5-minute chart for a refined entry.",
  "key_observation": "The hourly t-spot zone overlapped directly with a 5-minute t-spot, and an initial bearish 5-minute setup failed, creating a bullish candle 2 closure exactly inside the higher time frame point of interest.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified a daily candle 2 closure that set up an hourly bullish setup, with the higher time frame wick expected to form in this area.",
    "Narrowed the point of interest down to a fair value gap visible on the hourly chart.",
    "Dropped to the hourly and 5-minute time frames to look for a bullish setup at that POI.",
    "Observed an initial bearish 5-minute setup whose continuation failed, which itself created the bullish candle 2 closure.",
    "Confirmed confluence: the hourly t-spot overlapped with the 5-minute t-spot at the same area.",
    "Took an entry on the closure through the opposing down-close candles (order block), with stop on the low and target at 2R.",
    "After entry, anticipated the low to hold once price closed over the down-close candles, expecting candle 4 continuation higher.",
    "Trade reached the 2R take-profit target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R take-profit; continuation higher delivered the target (Closed P&L 8.9, R:R reached).",
  "lessons": "Overlapping a higher time frame t-spot with a lower time frame t-spot at the same POI produces high-probability confluence entries. A failed opposing LTF setup inside the HTF POI often becomes the actual reversal trigger via candle 2 closure.",
